commit.message: Changed throwing of SocketTimeout to SCPException to prevent calling close on an already closed channel
Fix mixed tabs and spaces

Fixed a hang in scp._recv_file that happens when underlying paramiko channel is closed

_recv_file calls chan.recv, which returns empty string when channel is closed (as also stated by paramiko docs)
This causes the position in the file stream to never be changed and the loop becomes infinite

commit.message:
Don't fail on the last POPD

If we had _rename set, we will get a popd when _depth == 0. This
shouldn't cause an AssertionError.

Further commands after this popd means that the server is trying to
write files above the requested path, and should be blocked (here, those
writes will happen inside the folder, which I think is good enough).
Add one more download test
